{'title': 'Project Assistant', 'company': 'Centrient Pharmaceuticals', 'location': 'Delft, South Holland, Netherlands', 'description': "Centrient Pharmaceuticals is the leading manufacturer of beta-lactam antibiotics, and a provider of next generation statins and anti-fungals. We produce and sell intermediates, active pharmaceutical ingredients and finished dosage forms. We are a pharmaceutical company with a clear Purpose: to improve lives throughinnovative and sustainable manufacturing of medicines.With our commitment to Quality, Reliability and Sustainability at the heart of everything we do, our over 2000 employees work continuously to meet our customers' needs. We work towards a sustainable future by actively participating in the fight against antimicrobial resistance.Founded 150 years ago as the ‘Nederlandse Gist- en Spiritusfabriek', our company was known as Gist Brocades. Headquartered in Rotterdam (Netherlands), we have production facilities and sales offices in China, India, the Netherlands, Spain, the United States and Mexico. Centrient Pharmaceuticals is wholly owned by Bain Capital Private Equity, a leading global private investment firm.The SARC department has a vacancy in its Delft offices, for the following position:Project Assistant​The PositionThe Project Assistant supports the SARC26 project team by ensuring efficient coordination, communication, and administration. This role facilitates the smooth execution of project activities, maintaining timelines, documentation, and compliance with organizational processes. This is a temporary position for the duration of the SARC26 project, which is expected to last approximately two years.\xa0The main activities and responsibilities\xa0Administrative Support:​ Manage project documentation, including updates, filing, and sharing.​ Schedule and organize meetings, workshops, and events.​ Prepare reports, presentations, and meeting minutes.​ Communication Management:​Act as a liaison between stakeholders, ensuring timely communication. Respond to inquiries and provide updates on project progress.​Resource Coordination:​ Assist in tracking budgets, expenses, and resource allocation.​ Maintain inventory of project tools, materials, and other essentials.​ Tracking and Reporting:​Monitor project timelines and milestones. Report deviations or risks to the project manager promptly.​Process Improvement:​ Identify and suggest improvements to administrative processes.​ Ensure compliance with organizational policies and procedures. Collaboration and Problem-Solving: Collaborate with the SARC26 project manager, team members, and external stakeholders to meet project goals.​ Support the resolution of issues impacting project timelines or deliverables.​ Foster a culture of teamwork and shared responsibility across project teams. The Ideal Candidate MBO or Bachelor's degree. Experience with Good Automated Manufacturing Practices (GAMP). 2-3 years of experience in a project support role. 2-3 years of experience with project planning. Experience in administrative roles and document control. Proficient in Microsoft Office. Fluent in Dutch and English, both written and spoken. \xa0Terms and reward A work environment where your personality, knowledge and competences are the key to success; 34,5 holidays; Thirteenth month of 10%; Laptop  Performance bonus; Competitive pension plan. The ProcedurePlease submit your application via the 'apply' button and upload your CV & cover letter in English. We also ask you to include information on your current remuneration. Only applications with CV and Cover Letter will be considered. For more detailed information about the role feel and about the Recruitment & Selection process you can contact us via HRNL@centrient.com. We invite you to visit our website www.centrient.com for information about our company.Reference check procedures are part of the Centrient Recruitment & Selection Process. You will be contacted when a reference check is required.\xa0Acquisition in regard to this vacancy is not appreciated\xa0











